10/08/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- High-ranking government officials attended roundtable discussions on national security in Belgrade on Friday (8 August).
The forum tackled defence reforms, EU and NATO integration, and problems in Kosovo.
Serbia-Montenegro Defence Minister Boris Tadic said Euro-Atlantic integration would be the best and fastest way to reduce threats to national security.
Army Chief of Staff Gen Branko Krga added that the army's main objective is to combat terrorism.
He stressed the need for a new, redefined military doctrine based on gradual transformation to a fully professional army.
Also participating in the forum was Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Goran Svilanovic, Serbian Deputy Prime Minister Nebojsa Covic, police representatives and representatives of religious communities.
(Tanjug, Beta, B92, BKTV - 08/08/03)
